                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know that charm is overpowered, but there's got to be a more fair way of nerfing it. My mob does half the damage it used to but when it breaks it can still wipe my group in seconds. It's not worth using charm in oow because of that. =/
<br />

<br />
I would love it if they put in lvl 46-47 mobs (to high for DC in other words) that con indiff to all and are charmable. They'd be too high for DC, but could hit for roughly 50% of what the average mob in the zone hits for and do that all the time reguardless of whether they're charmed or not. That to me would be fair. I get 50% of the damage but there's a chance my pet won't instantly kill me when it breaks (frankly most normal mobs would). 50% of what a normal mob can do is still alot when you're a soft squishy caster.
<br />

<br />
And as far as charming elementals in BoT those guys are really really user friendly. There's lots of space to run around in BoT and those don't hit nearly as hard as some stuff does now (yah, I know they can still squish me if they wanted). There's no room in NC at all to get away from a homicidal ex-pet that's about to splatter you now that it can hit for it's full dps again. You pretty much got death to look forward to if you charm there. Why does sony want chanters to try tanking things that most tanks can't handle without slows when we don't even get war's damage mitigation?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
