                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nanyea The Wayward wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Llondo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Hate to disagree with you Nanyea but wizards cannot do high 700's sustainable.  We can burst probably just about that..maybe a tad higher, but we cannot sustain that in an exp group.  </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Id consider chaining for 20 mins while sittin on horse with 100+ mana regen sustainable on raids...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
SK/Necro pumping mana at the wizard?  Bard in group +% damaging wizard?  BST Paragoning?
<br />

<br />
Base wizard nuke ratio (Ancient GoD): 4.28
<br />
+23% from crits, +38% from foci = * 1.61
<br />
* 100% / (100% - 25% (SCM/Spec) - 12.5% (foci)) = * 1.60
<br />
----
<br />
* 2.58
<br />

<br />
4.28 * 2.58 = 11 damage:mana.
<br />

<br />
700 DPS = 4200 Dam/Tick = 381.8 mana drain/tick
<br />

<br />
120 mana/tick (passive buffs) + 11 mana/tick per SK + 27 mana/tick per necro + 20 mana/tick from rods/robes/MGB paragons etc
<br />

<br />
So, lets say 3 SKs and 2 necros (insane!)
<br />

<br />
Total mana regen of 227 mana/tick.
<br />

<br />
Net deficit of 154 mana/tick.  20 minutes = 200 ticks = 30800 net mana lost.
<br />

<br />
Going at it the other way, over 200 ticks the wizard lost at most 10000 mana, or a max deficit of 50 mana/tick.
<br />

<br />
So the wizard needs to be gaingin 330 mana/tick.  He's short 100 mana/tick.  Two necros chain twitching the wizard can sustain that!
<br />

<br />
Ok, so a wizard with 3 SKs in their group, 2 necros (both of which are chain twitching the wizard), mobs with mana pools always in camp, using a mana robe, with 10 k mana pool, can manage 700 DPS sustained!
<br />

<br />
(that's 700 DPS * 20 minutes = 840 k damage over those 20 minutes)
<br />

<br />
Or, was that 20 minutes of time, during which you parsed the wizard DPS during fights?  That wouldn't require quite the same extreme setup.
<br />

<br />
(as an aside, a wizard chain-casting his GoD ancient nuke does 750 DPS.  I don't know where this wizard managed the time to mana robe/click on mod rods/etc -- I guess not every recast time was used to concuss).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
