<br />
Hate to disagree with you Nanyea but wizards cannot do high 700's sustainable.  We can burst probably just about that..maybe a tad higher, but we cannot sustain that in an exp group.  
<br />
To gain 700 plus dps we would need to chain White Fire, and have Elemental right clicky concussion which can be cast during the 2.5 second spell gem refresh timer.  Unfortunately Mana regen does not allow you to chain White Fire without some significant downtime.  
<br />
With Omens mobs having so many HP we actually probably are decreasing our DPS just to keep up with mana regen.
<br />
During an exp group wizards are closer to 300 to 350 dps at the high end.  I can hit 900dps burst damage, but thats for a very short amount of time and I am Time geared.
<br />

<br />
Rogues do higher sustained DPS as they have no mana bar to worry about.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Agree, am time/OoW equipped as well (clicky leg and staff of temp flux max pre-OoW crit AAs and first of OoW) havent gotten all my GoD spells yet but burst can break 1k+ if I get lucky but sustained is likely somewhere around 300-500 depending on mob, resists, debuffs, mana regen status (horse, etc.). Course depends how you defined sustained? One high hp mob over lets say 3-5 mins on who I unload my whole manabar? Or semi-perm in a 75%+ uptime xp grp.
<br />

<br />
My def would be 75%+ uptime xp grp where rogues and even high-end melee centric rangers (of which I have one) would match or beat my dps. Course uptime is key to melee dps just like mana is key to caster dps.
<br />

<br />
EDIT cause of later posts - and 20 mins is not sustained. 20 mins then 10 minutes rest. That is gonna cut the damage by 1/3 on a truly sustainable basis. Melee will sustain so long as their is a target and they are alive. It is possible to always have a target (park them in camp), its not alway possible to nuke. Oh and wiz nerf incoming cause a handful of wizs can sustain 5-600dps for any length of time. Highest rogue I have seen is 550-600 sustained with disc pre-OoW.
