                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just so those who don't like numbers understand:
<br />

<br />
To hit Nany's claimed "sustained wizard DPS for 20 minutes", I needed to have 3 SKs in the group, 2  necros in the group, with both necros chain-casting twitches to keep the wizard's mana pool full.  The wizard literally didn't stop casting for those 20 minutes to realize 700 DPS, so uptime was basically 100%.
<br />

<br />
In other words, I don't believe a wizard did 840 k damage in 20 minutes (aka, 700 DPS sustained for 20 minutes), unless he has 2 necro lovers who like to make him look good.
<br />

<br />
By the same math, the 100% uptime infinitely sustained wizard DPS in a group with 100 mana/tick is 183.  No group hits 100% uptime -- 50% uptime is actually really decent (remember, you have to count bio breaks).  75% uptime is an insane-pull group.  I have yet to see a parse over 85% uptime that went on for any length of time.
<br />

<br />
So that puts GoD wizard nuking at 244 to 366.
<br />

<br />
You can manage 130+ mana/tick with a mana robe etc, that would up endgame GoD wizard to 317 to 475 (depending on uptime).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
