                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually, the raid thing shouldn't be ignored because it is common across the classes IMO. The way it looks now, Everquest II will become the quest-based, lower-level solo and single group game with Everquest I being the raid-based game. i.e. If you plan to continue playing Everquest I, I hope you like to raid because that's the future of this game. We see this evidenced by the comment about mob scaling faster than PC scaling.
<br />

<br />
That said, the main problems *I* have with the game are, yes, group boredom and LFG boredom. The one is bad now... I'm truly worried the other will only get worse.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361216" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ariu <span style="font-style: italic">stop destroying my class damnit!</span> Vil''''Aki &lt;Heroes&gt;</a>
