                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Trying to bring the topic back to the original question:
<br />

<br />
Wizard - didn't care either way
<br />
Mage - hahahah yay
<br />
Warrior - crap
<br />
Pally - Get rid of it, *I* have more dps than *that* thing (ACTUAL QUOTE ON DAY ONE OF OOW)
<br />
SK - didn't care either way, but frowned heavily when asking me to MPG and I said 'No Mez'
<br />
Rogue - cheered, proceeding to tell me how they've been nerfed since Kunark
<br />
Monk - didn't care either way
<br />
Druid - laughed, until realizing it means THEM too.
<br />
Necro - just laughed
<br />
Shammy - didn't like the idea of anyone getting mutilated to the point of being buffbots with a (linked) nuke
<br />

<br />
Fact is, most classes simply don't care. They have their own problems.
<br />
The thing is, I don't really care about charm being nerfed. I DO care about having all our abilities that make us special and desirable taken away one by one, be that through actual nerfing, or by designing content to make the use of the ability impossible.
<br />

<br />
We have by far the crappiest Epic out there. BY FAR. A clicky rune that agros when it drops and a mez modifier when in most places where you would like to be able to mez - you can't. Not only that, mix enchanter with Epic Necro Pet and you have a complete nightmare on your hands. The pet BREAKS MEZ, and not only that, it breaks Stasis as well. It can also not be called off. Great going SOE.
<br />

<br />
There are some issues that will come to light over time that will result in some people changing their minds about supporting enchanters. Not about the charm nerf, but about our usefulness overall.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
